block content

  style body{background: transparent url("http://punnitimages.s3-website-us-east-1.amazonaws.com/LAA.jpg") no-repeat scroll left top / cover !important;}

  div#introDiv

    h1 Multi-variable To-do List

    p A todo list with bivariate priority ranking: generates a priority for your tasks using both the weight of the assignment in the course, and the time left until the deadline:

    img(src="images/eq.svg",style="width:20em;padding-left:2em;")

    p (The dates are in Excel timestamp format, the weight is a fraction, and the priority is multiplied by 10<sup>2</sup> for display.)
 
    p Higher-weighted, sooner-due tasks receive higher priority. Tasks due within seven days are highlighted red, tasks due within fourteen days are highlighted yellow. The background image is configurable in the preferences.

    p Source code is #[a(href="https://github.com/davidschlachter/multivariable-todo") on Github].

    img(src="images/tasks.png",style="width:100%;")

